Class SessionCallStateMachine

java.lang.Object
  com.cornell.opencomm.jingleimpl.sessionmgmt.SessionCallStateMachine

public class SessionCallStateMachine
extends Object

This class defines all the states that a Jingle session can be in at any point in time.

getSessionState

Returns the current state of this session

Returns:

changeSessionState

public boolean changeSessionState(String action)
Changes the sessionState based on the attributeAction of the received OR outgoing JingleIQPacket . Returns success/failure of the state change based on whether it is legal to receive the particular attributeAction for a particular sessionState.

Parameters:
action - The attributeAction of the received or outgoing JingleIQPacket
Returns:
true on success, false on failure

setSessionState

public void setSessionState(int state)
Sets the sessionState to a desired value. This method is called when setting the state based on a RESULT ack IQ packet as there is no Action attribute in such an IQ Packet

Parameters:
state - the new state

getSessionStateString

public String getSessionStateString()
Returns the String form of the current sessionState to facilitate Logging

Returns:
String representation of sessionState
